properties.headline: CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS -  Wollongong Education Precinct - WOLLONGONG Princes Motorway, Memorial Drive at University of Wollongong
properties.adviceB: Use diversions; Allow extra travel time
properties.otherAdvice:
Traffic management will be in place around University of Wollongong during morning peak periods to help ease congestion and queuing on the M1 Princes Motorway.

From 7:45am to 9:15am Monday to Friday:

  • M1 Princes Mwy southbound traffic exiting at University Ave will be diverted left to make a U-turn at the eastern roundabout.
  • Traffic at Irvine St will diverted left, to the University Western Access route.
  • Motorists wishing to access the M1 Princes Mwy northbound ramp (towards Sydney) at Northfields Ave will be diverted via Murphys Ave and Robsons Rd.

Motorists should allow extra travel time during morning peak and follow instructions of traffic controllers.

CHANGED TRAFFIC CONDITIONS - KIRRIBILLI Warringah Freeway / Bradfield Highway approaching Sydney Harbour Bridge
properties.otherAdvice:
All southbound lanes approaching the Harbour Bridge including the Cahill Expressway will be closed between 8:10am and 8:30am approximately while vintage cars travel across the bridge in a Police escorted convoy for the Sydney Harbour Bridge 90th Anniversary event.

Motorists travelling southbound will be diverted into the Harbour Tunnel. Oversize (over 4.4m) & Dangerous Goods Vehicles will need to travel via the Gladesville Bridge and Victoria Rd during this time.

Lane 4 northbound on the Sydney Harbour Bridge will also be closed and the speed limit will be reduced to 40km/h across the bridge. Northbound traffic will remain unaffected and can continue across the Harbour Bridge in lanes 1-3.
